{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QB69jVqNVEDtbJppu9ioNu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.example.orderspring.repository;\n     2→\n     3→import com.example.orderspring.entity.CustomerOrder;\n     4→import org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository;\n     5→import org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.Query;\n     6→import org.springframework.stereotype.Repository;\n     7→\n     8→import java.util.List;\n     9→\n    10→@Repository\n    11→public interface CustomerOrderRepository extends JpaRepository<CustomerOrder, Integer> {\n    12→    \n    13→    @Query(\"SELECT co FROM CustomerOrder co ORDER BY co.orderId\")\n    14→    List<CustomerOrder> findAllOrders();\n    15→}\n    16→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8913198c-9d1c-4b4e-afa3-ca816a8bda5a","uuid":"d3d47716-5537-4ee1-8985-4d6e0954cfc5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FbjyZsffxJq9j4jhh4YoSV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.example.orderspring.repository;\n     2→\n     3→import com.example.orderspring.entity.LineItem;\n     4→import com.example.orderspring.entity.LineItemKey;\n     5→import org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository;\n     6→import org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.Query;\n     7→import org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.Modifying;\n     8→import org.springframework.data.repository.query.Param;\n     9→import org.springframework.stereotype.Repository;\n    10→\n    11→import java.util.List;\n    12→\n    13→@Repository\n    14→public interface LineItemRepository extends JpaRepository<LineItem, LineItemKey> {\n    15→    \n    16→    @Query(\"SELECT l FROM LineItem l\")\n    17→    List<LineItem> findAllLineItems();\n    18→    \n    19→    @Query(\"SELECT l FROM LineItem l WHERE l.customerOrder.orderId = :orderId ORDER BY l.itemId\")\n    20→    List<LineItem> findLineItemsByOrderId(@Param(\"orderId\") Integer orderId);\n    21→    \n    22→    @Query(\"SELECT DISTINCT l FROM LineItem l WHERE l.itemId = :itemId AND l.customerOrder.orderId = :orderId\")\n    23→    LineItem findLineItemById(@Param(\"itemId\") int itemId, @Param(\"orderId\") Integer orderId);\n    24→\n    25→    @Modifying(clearAutomatically = true, flushAutomatically = true)\n    26→    @Query(\"DELETE FROM LineItem l WHERE l.customerOrder.orderId = :orderId\")\n    27→    void deleteAllByOrderId(@Param(\"orderId\") Integer orderId);\n    28→\n    29→}\n    30→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":nul