{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_017HvjS9wZmwfJcYPcKShkHf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good. Now let me update the todo and begin the major migration work. I need to think carefully about the best Jakarta EE approach.\n\n**Strategy Decision:** The cleanest approach is to use **Payara Micro** or **WildFly** as the Jakarta EE runtime. However, another practical approach is to simply update Spring Boot to properly be a pure Jakarta EE app. Given the project uses JoinFaces (which integrates JSF with Spring), the \"migration from Spring to Jakarta\" likely means:\n\n1. Remove Spring Boot framework\n2. Use a Jakarta EE application server (like Payara Micro) \n3. Replace Spring Data JPA with plain EntityManager\n4. Replace Spring annotations with CDI annotations\n5. Use a WAR deployment to a Jakarta EE container\n\nLet me implement this approach using **Payara Micro** (lightweight Jakarta EE runtime):"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":879,"cache_read_input_tokens":54997,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":879,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":767},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8913198c-9d1c-4b4e-afa3-ca816a8bda5a","uuid":"8fff33d8-1306-4672-bfaa-0e9607b5e66a"}
