{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EEvuqrakVCft7dGuQhwxG1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<persistence version=\"3.0\" xmlns=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/persistence\"\n     3→             xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n     4→             xsi:schemaLocation=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/persistence https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/persistence/persistence_3_0.xsd\">\n     5→\n     6→    <persistence-unit name=\"orderPU\" transaction-type=\"JTA\">\n     7→        <jta-data-source>java:app/jdbc/orderDS</jta-data-source>\n     8→        <class>com.example.orderspring.entity.CustomerOrder</class>\n     9→        <class>com.example.orderspring.entity.LineItem</class>\n    10→        <class>com.example.orderspring.entity.Part</class>\n    11→        <class>com.example.orderspring.entity.VendorPart</class>\n    12→        <class>com.example.orderspring.entity.Vendor</class>\n    13→        <properties>\n    14→            <property name=\"jakarta.persistence.schema-generation.database.action\" value=\"drop-and-create\"/>\n    15→            <property name=\"hibernate.show_sql\" value=\"true\"/>\n    16→            <property name=\"hibernate.format_sql\" value=\"true\"/>\n    17→            <property name=\"hibernate.dialect\" value=\"org.hibernate.dialect.H2Dialect\"/>\n    18→        </properties>\n    19→    </persistence-unit>\n    20→</persistence>\n    21→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8913198c-9d1c-4b4e-afa3-ca816a8bda5a","uuid":"7db32146-4ca2-4966-9c05-f66bff4f8fb4"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013GXt74eZ111JVKkdvFH8ax","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<web-app xmlns=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee\"\n     3→         xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n     4→         xsi:schemaLocation=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee/web-app_6_0.xsd\"\n     5→         version=\"6.0\">\n     6→\n     7→    <display-name>Order Jakarta EE Application</display-name>\n     8→\n     9→    <context-param>\n    10→        <param-name>jakarta.faces.PROJECT_STAGE</param-name>\n    11→        <param-value>Development</param-value>\n    12→    </context-param>\n    13→\n    14→    <context-param>\n    15→        <param-name>primefaces.THEME</param-name>\n    16→        <param-value>saga</param-value>\n    17→    </context-param>\n    18→\n    19→    <servlet>\n    20→        <servlet-name>Faces Servlet</servlet-name>\n    21→        <servlet-class>jakarta.faces.webapp.FacesServlet</servlet-class>\n    22→        <load-on-startup>1</load-on-startup>\n    23→    </servlet>\n    24→\n    25→    <servlet-mapping>\n    26→        <servlet-name>Faces Servlet</servlet-name>\n    27→        <url-pattern>*.xhtml</url-pattern>\n    28→    </servlet-mapping>\n    29→\n    30→    <welcome-file-list>\n    31→        <welcome-file>order.xhtml</welcome-file>\n    32→    </welcome-file-list>\n    33→\n    34→    <data-source>\n    35→        <name>java:app/jdbc/orderDS</name>\n    36→        <class-name>org.h2.jdbcx.JdbcDataSource</class-name>\n    37→        <url>jdbc:h2:mem:testdb;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1</url>\n    38→        <user>sa</user>\n    39→        <password></password>\n    40→    </data-source>\n    41→</web-app>\n    42→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8913198c-9d1c-4b4e-afa3-ca816a8bda5a","uuid":"fb9b6cdb-ed39-4ab0-8f5b-46b72a7a88ea"}
