{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_014FcN7mz2ZBMsysTYPBFzK4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Dockerfile is correct. But the `maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble` base image has a weird entrypoint that's not being reset by `ENTRYPOINT []`. Interestingly though, the app IS running and deployed on Open Liberty which IS a Jakarta EE 10 runtime. The logs show:\n\n```\n[AUDIT] CWWKZ0001I: Application order-jakarta started in 41.507 seconds.\n```\n\nSo the application successfully deployed! The Open Liberty server that's embedded in the Maven image already has Jakarta EE 10 support. But it reads a `server.xml` that has a different datasource config. The actual working config is coming from the `server.xml` file that was already present in the image.\n\nLet me check what happened - the logs show the app actually loaded with tables being dropped (which is the `drop-and-create` behavior). And Open Liberty detected the `data-source` from web.xml. Let me try accessing the app:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":623,"cache_read_input_tokens":145599,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":623,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":330},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8913198c-9d1c-4b4e-afa3-ca816a8bda5a","uuid":"d0bbb08e-eae4-4f06-b958-a9f4d8c6e441"}
